OL,6,FDefending O'Brien, Steve Burnell said
OL,7,Fit was his understanding police had
OL,8,Farrested his client and removed his
OL,9,Fphone the day before the fire after
OL,10,Fthe defendant made between 30 and 40
OL,11,Fcalls to the police.
OL,13,FJudge Wayne Beard said pre-sentence
OL,14,Fand psychiatric reports on the
OL,15,Fdefendant suggested he seemed to have
OL,16,Fbeen experiencing paranoid-type
OL,17,Fthoughts, although there was no
OL,18,Fpsychiatric illness needing hospital
OL,19,Ftreatment.
